excerpt: Funchal is the capital city of Portugal's Madeira archipelago. It's backed by hills, and known for its harbor, gardens and Madeira wine cellars. The centuries-old Funchal Cathedral, which mixes Gothic and Romanesque styles, is notable for its carved wooden ceiling. Fronting the harbor is the São Tiago Fortress, built in the 1600s. It now houses the Contemporary Art Museum, with a large collection of Portuguese works.
detail_description: Funchal, the capital city of Portugal's Madeira archipelago, is a charming destination backed by hills and renowned for its harbor, gardens, and Madeira wine cellars. The city boasts the centuries-old Funchal Cathedral with its unique mix of Gothic and Romanesque styles and the São Tiago Fortress, now home to the Contemporary Art Museum. Visitors can explore the city at their leisure, taking a cable car up to the botanical gardens and Monte Palace.
name: Funchal
address: Portugal

excerpt: Hillside botanical gardens with a bird park, natural history museum & glass houses, plus sea views.
detail_description: The Madeira Botanical Garden is a hillside paradise boasting a bird park, natural history museum, and glass houses with stunning sea views. This modern marvel of contemporary architecture, co-designed by renowned architects Abalos & Herreros, features a unique latticed wooden canopy providing shade and dynamic interplay between light and shadow. The garden's design seamlessly blends with nature, offering visitors an immersive experience. Additionally, the Nini Design Center provides innovative spaces for exhibitions and workshops.
name: Madeira Botanical Garden
address: 9060-345 Funchal, Portugal

excerpt: Traditional indoor facility built in 1940 featuring merchants of produce, flowers & seafood.
detail_description: Mercado dos Lavradores, a traditional indoor market established in 1940, is a popular attraction in Funchal. It offers an array of goods including fresh produce, flowers, and seafood. Visitors can explore the vibrant fruit stands showcasing guavas, dragon fruits, and lychees while enjoying a drink at the Madeira Beer Lab. The market also features a bustling fish section and flower stalls where locals sell beautiful blooms in traditional attire.
name: Mercado dos Lavradores
address: Largo dos Lavradores, 9060-158 Funchal, Portugal

excerpt: Large, garden-like park with diverse trees, flower beds & walkways, plus a lake with ducks & swans.
detail_description: Santa Catarina Park is a spacious garden-like park in Madeira, featuring a variety of trees, flower beds, and walkways. Visitors can enjoy picnics by the lake while children have fun at the playground or feed ducks and swans. The park offers stunning views of Funchal Bay and provides a playroom for kids to engage in activities. Additionally, renting a bicycle to explore the large park or Funchal is an option.
name: Parque de Santa Catarina
address: Av. do Infante 18, São Martinho, 9000-015 Funchal, Portugal

excerpt: Gothic-style, late-15th-century Catholic church with an ornate interior comprising 3 naves.
detail_description: Funchal Cathedral, a Gothic-style Catholic church dating back to the late 15th century, boasts an elaborate interior with three naves. The island of Madeira in the Atlantic Ocean is a stunning destination, abundant with vibrant flowers and aromatic fruits. Its volcanic landscape creates towering cliffs that offer breathtaking ocean views and conceal diverse wildlife and plant species. While Madeira is renowned for its tropical nature and botanical gardens, it also features well-developed cities with museums showcasing the island's rich history.
name: Funchal Cathedral
address: R. do Aljube, São Martinho, 9000-067 Funchal, Portugal

excerpt: Museum spotlighting the famous footballer Cristiano Ronaldo featuring his career history & trophies.
detail_description: The CR7 Museum, located in Madeira Island, is a dedicated space showcasing the remarkable career of renowned footballer Cristiano Ronaldo. Visitors can delve into his journey through an array of exhibits including photographs, videos, interactive displays, and an impressive collection of over a hundred individual and team trophies earned while playing for various teams.
name: CR7 Museum
address: Praça CR7, Av. Sá Carneiro 27, São Martinho, 9004-518 Funchal, Portugal

excerpt: Lined with shops & cafes, the city's oldest street features doors painted by local & global artists.
detail_description: Rua de Santa Maria, located in the Old Town of Funchal, is a vibrant and historic street known for its colorful doors adorned with artwork by local and international artists. This pedestrianized lane is part of the Arte de Portas Abertas project, which aimed to revitalize the area after a tropical storm in 2010.
name: Rua de Santa Maria
address: 9060-291 Funchal, Portugal

excerpt: Enormous, yellow-hued fort built in the 17th century to defend the city from attacks by pirates.
detail_description: Forte de São Tiago, a massive yellow fort constructed in the 17th century, was built to protect the city from pirate invasions. Originally erected in response to attacks by English, French, Algerian, and Turkish pirates drawn to Funchal's thriving sugar trade, the fortress now houses the Contemporary Art Museum. Visitors can explore its intricate passages and tower for breathtaking views of Funchal.
name: Forte de São Tiago
address: Tv. do Forte 8, 9060-123 Funchal, Portugal

excerpt: Sea & mountain views attract riders of this modern gondola running from Funchal to Monte.
detail_description: The Funchal Cable Car is a modern gondola that takes riders from Funchal to Monte, offering stunning views of the sea and mountains. The 20-minute ride provides a unique perspective of the city, with winding streets and clusters of houses resembling tiny models on a living map. At Monte, visitors can explore tropical gardens featuring exotic plants, flowers, and various animals.
name: Funchal Cable Car
address: Av. do Mar e das Comunidades Madeirenses, 9060-190 Funchal, Portugal

excerpt: Samples & guided tours exploring Madeira wine production. barrel making & storage.
detail_description: Blandy's Wine Lodge offers samples and guided tours that provide an in-depth exploration of Madeira wine production, including barrel making and storage. Established in 1811, this family-run business provides a fascinating insight into the unique history and aging process of Madeira wines. Visitors can tour the warehouse filled with wooden barrels where the finest vintages are aged using the traditional canteiro method.
name: Blandy's Wine Lodge
address: Av. Arriaga 28, São Martinho, 9000-064 Funchal, Portugal

excerpt: A road reaches this 1,818-meter high peak, with a cafe & gift shop, that often looks down on clouds.
detail_description: Pico do Arieiro is one of the highest peaks in Madeira, reaching 1,818 meters above sea level. Visitors can drive up to this peak and enjoy a cafe and gift shop with stunning views that often overlook the clouds. The area offers a magical experience, especially during sunrise or sunset when the sky is painted in beautiful colors.
name: Pico do Arieiro
address: Portugal

excerpt: Unique, modern museum with interactive exhibits of Madeira's history, plus a bistro with a terrace.
detail_description: Located in the heart of Funchal's Old Town, Madeira Story Centre is a unique and modern museum that offers interactive exhibits showcasing the history of Madeira. Visitors can take a virtual journey through time, experiencing significant events from the volcanic formation millions of years ago to historical figures like Prince Henry the Navigator and Churchill. The museum provides insights into Madeira's discovery, its volcanic origins, and its cultural heritage.
name: Madeira Story Centre
address: R. Dom Carlos I 27, 9060-051 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: Igreja de São João Evangelista do Colégio do Funchal, also known as the College Church, is a significant religious site in Funchal. This 17th-century Baroque church was constructed by the Jesuits and boasts an intricate facade adorned with ornamental stonework and statues of saints. Inside, visitors are greeted by opulent gold leaf decorations covering the walls, columns, and altar.
name: Igreja de São João Evangelista do Colégio do Funchal
address: Largo do Colégio, São Martinho, 9000-000 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: Nestled on the southern coast of Madeira, Doca do Cavacas is a hidden gem that perfectly blends relaxation and stunning natural beauty. This charming beach, also known as Poca do Gomes, lies conveniently between the Lido and Formosa beach in Funchal. With its inviting volcanic swimming pool and direct sea access, it offers breathtaking views of the Atlantic Ocean and Cabo Girao skywalk—the highest cliff in Europe.
name: Doca do Cavacas
address: Rua da Ponta da Cruz 66, 9000-250 Funchal, Portugal

excerpt: Landscaped green space showcasing tropical plants in a hillside venue overlooking the ocean.
detail_description: Palheiro Gardens is a stunning hillside venue that offers breathtaking views of the ocean and showcases a variety of tropical plants. The gardens originated in the early 1800s when exotic trees from around the world were planted, and over time, more exotics were introduced, creating an impressive ensemble of gardens including the Main Garden, Sunken Garden, Ribeiro do Inferno, Rose Garden, and Ladys Garden.
name: Palheiro Gardens
address: Caminho da Quinta do Palheiro , 32 São Gonçalo, 9060-255 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: Old Town | Bar & Lounge | is a captivating destination that invites you to explore the historic heart of Funchal, Portugal. As you stroll along its charming cobbled streets and squares, you'll encounter a blend of rich architectural heritage and vibrant street art that reflects Madeiran culture. Notable highlights include Rua da Santa Maria, where colorful murals celebrate local icons like fado singer Amalia and football star Cristiano Ronaldo.
name: Old Town | Bar & Lounge |
address: Tv. das Torres 6, 9060-314 Funchal, Portugal

excerpt: Big, multi-level garden with exotic trees & flowers, ponds, African sculptures & a mineral museum.
detail_description: Monte Palace Tropical Garden, located in Madeira, is a stunning garden surrounding the former pleasure estate and luxury hotel Quinta Monte Palace. The garden boasts a diverse collection of exotic plants from around the world as well as rare native species from Madeira. Created by local entrepreneur Joe Berardo in the late 1980s, this garden features an array of trees, flowers, fountains, ponds, waterfalls, statues, and Japanese-themed gardens with pagodas and carp ponds.
name: Jardim Monte Palace Madeira
address: Caminho das Babosas 4 A, Monte, 9050-288 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: Marina do Funchal is a charming waterfront destination in the heart of Funchal, offering a picturesque setting for leisurely strolls and exciting excursions. The marina boasts wide promenades along the sea, lined with lush green spaces and Portuguese pavement walkways. Visitors can explore the area's numerous bars and upscale restaurants while taking in stunning views of the yachts moored at its 210-berth facility.
name: Marina do Funchal
address: São Martinho, Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: The Convent of Santa Clara, situated in Funchal, Portugal, is a must-see historical site dating back to the 15th century. Founded by Joao Goncalves da Camara, it offers a captivating insight into the region's religious and architectural legacy. The convent boasts remarkable Gothic and Manueline-style architecture with intricate details and beautiful archways.
name: Convent of Santa Clara
address: Calçada de Santa Clara 15, São Martinho, 9000-036 Funchal, Portugal

excerpt: 500 years of art, ceramics, jewelry & antiques housed in an 18th-century villa in lush gardens.
detail_description: Quinta das Cruzes Museum is a historical gem located in an 18th-century villa surrounded by lush gardens. Once the residence of Funchal's second captain, this baroque-style quinta now houses a remarkable decorative art museum.
name: Quinta das Cruzes Museum
address: Calçada do Pico, nº1, 9000-206 Funchal, Portugal
